Welcome to Audio Augmentation’s documentation!

Audio Augmentation Methods

class src.data_aug.audio_augmentation.Augmenter(input_signal: ndarray, file_name: str, config: Optional[dict] = None)

A class to represent audio augmenter. Currently, supported augmentation methods: time_stretch, pitch_shift, volume_control, time_shift and add_noise.

add_noise(snr_db: int) → ndarray

This method adds noise by specified snr. Args:

snr_db: Signal-Noise-Ratio (SNR)

Returns: The audio time-series with added white noise.

pitch_shift(sr: int, bins_per_octave: int, n_steps: int) → ndarray

This method shifts pitch of input signal by specified number of steps. Args:

sr: Sampling rate bins_per_octave: Bins per octave n_steps: Number of fractional steps to shift. (A step is equal to a semitone if bins_per_octave is set to 12.)

Returns: The pitch-shifted audio time-series.

time_shift(shift_pct: int) → ndarray

This method shifts input signal in time by given percentage Args:

shift_pct: Time shift in percents.

Returns: Time shifted audio time-series.

time_stretch(rate=None) → ndarray

This method speeds up or slows down input signal by given rate. Args:

rate: Stretch factor (Real positive scalar). If rate>1 the signal is speed up. If rate<1 the signal is slowed down.

Returns: Audio time series stretched by the specified rate.

volume_control(gain_dB: int) → ndarray

This method controls volume of input signal. Args:

gain_dB: Volume gain in dB.

Returns: The audio time-series with increased or decreased volume.

Routines - Augmentation Approaches

src.routines.augmentation.run_parallel_augmentation(input_signal_path: Path, config: dict, methods: list, n_methods: int, export: bool, export_path: Optional[Path] = None)

This function applies parallel data augmentation on a given input signal. Args:

input_signal_path: Path to input signal (time series data). config: Config. methods: List of audio augmentation methods. n_methods: Number of random methods picked from a list of methods. export: Save outputs (True/False) export_path: Export path.

Returns: List of augmented time series.

src.routines.augmentation.run_sequential_augmentation(input_signal_path: Path, config: dict, sequence: list, export: bool, export_path: Optional[Path] = None) → tuple

This function applies sequence of augmentation methods on a given input signal. Args:

input_signal_path: Path to input signal (time series data). config: Config file. sequence: List (sequence) of augmentation methods. export: Save outputs (True/False) export_path: Export path.

Returns: Augmented signal and augmented filename.

Returns: Generated suffix as a string.
